{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 12:37:28.618908", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report — SDN Spine–Leaf Topology\n\nScope\n- Topology: OVS leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1; hosts host_1_1, host_1_2 (on leaf_1) and host_2_1, host_2_2 (on leaf_2). All hosts in 10.0.0.0/24. Controller at 20.0.0.100 via OpenFlow.\n- Objective: Assess current network health, identify anomalies, localize faulty devices, determine root cause. No remediation proposed.\n\n1) Network Health Assessment and Anomalies Detected\n- Connectivity is severely degraded. Only one host pair communicates; all other intra-/inter-leaf traffic fails.\n  - Working:\n    - host_2_1 (10.0.0.3) -> host_1_2 (10.0.0.2): 0% loss, ~3 ms RTT.\n    - Return path host_1_2 -> host_2_1 also functional (as inferred from symmetric OpenFlow entries).\n  - Failing:\n    - host_1_1 (10.0.0.1) <-> host_1_2 (10.0.0.2): failures (Destination Host Unreachable/timeout).\n    - host_1_1 <-> host_2_1, host_1_1 <-> host_2_2, host_1_2 <-> host_2_2, host_2_1 <-> host_2_2: failures (timeouts or “Destination Host Unreachable”).\n- ARP resolution issues widespread:\n  - ip neigh shows many FAILED entries (e.g., on host_1_1 and host_2_2). Only host_1_2 has a STALE entry for 10.0.0.3, consistent with the single working pair.\n- Link layer appears healthy:\n  - All OVS data ports (eth0/eth1/eth2 on leafs; eth0/eth1 on spine) report state LIVE at 10Gbps.\n  - Controllers show is_connected: true on all switches.\n- The switches are in fail_mode: secure, meaning traffic without controller-installed flows is dropped (no default learning/flooding).\n\n2) Localization of the Fault\n- Hosts are correctly configured:\n  - Each host has 10.0.0.X/24 on eth0 with the expected on-link route; interfaces are UP; no local NIC issues indicated.\n- Data-plane links are not the issue:\n  - OVS port states are LIVE; no errors reported.\n- Anomalous behavior is on the switches’ OpenFlow tables, specifically leaf_1 and leaf_2, with corroboration on spine_1:\n  - leaf_1 flows:\n    - in_port=1 actions=output:1 (hairpin back to same port), n_packets=44.\n    - Specific unicast MAC-to-MAC rules only for host_1_2 <-> host_2_1 via uplink (ports 2 and 3).\n    - No broadcast/ARP handling or rules for host_1_1 or host_2_2.\n  - leaf_2 flows:\n    - in_port=2 actions=output:2 (hairpin), n_packets=36.\n    - Specific unicast MAC-to-MAC rules only for host_2_1 <-> host_1_2 via uplink (ports 1 and 3).\n    - No broadcast/ARP handling or rules for host_2_2 or host_1_1.\n  - spine_1 flows:\n    - Only the two unicast rules for the working host_1_2 ↔ host_2_1 pair.\n    - No broadcast/unknown handling.\n- Consequence:\n  - host_1_1 (leaf_1 port 1) traffic is hairpinned back to its ingress port and never forwarded → cannot reach anyone (even local host_1_2).\n  - host_2_2 (leaf_2 port 2) traffic is hairpinned similarly → cannot reach anyone.\n  - ARP broadcast/unknown traffic is not flooded/forwarded due to fail_mode secure and lack of broadcast flows → widespread ARP failures and “Destination Host Unreachable.”\n\n3) Root Cause Analysis\n- Root cause: Incorrect OpenFlow programming by the SDN controller.\n  - Evidence:\n    - Hairpin flows present on leaf_1 (in_port=1 -> output:1) and leaf_2 (in_port=2 -> output:2), which blackhole traffic from host_1_1 and host_2_2, respectively.\n    - Only per-MAC unicast flows are installed for one specific pair (host_1_2 <-> host_2_1), leaving all other destinations unhandled.\n    - No flows to handle broadcast/ARP/unknown unicast; with fail_mode=secure, the default behavior is to drop, causing ARP failures across the fabric.\n  - Controller connectivity is up on all switches, so this is not a control-plane reachability issue but a logic/policy error in the flow rules pushed by the controller.\n\nAdditional Observations\n- The described topology mentions spine_1:eth2 <-> leaf_1:eth3, but runtime port descriptions show only eth0/eth1 on spine_1 and eth0/eth1/eth2 on leaf_1. This discrepancy does not explain the observed failures (links present are LIVE), but indicates configuration drift from the described diagram.\n\nConclusion\n- The network is in a degraded state due to controller-installed OpenFlow rules that:\n  - Hairpin traffic on certain leaf access ports.\n  - Install unicast rules for only a single host pair.\n  - Omit broadcast/ARP handling under secure fail mode.\n- Fault localized to SDN control-plane policy/logic (rules on leaf_1, leaf_2, and spine_1), not host configuration or physical links.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9253, "output_tokens": 4584, "total_tokens": 13837, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7680}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3328}}}
